<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2014, &ldquo;How Truth Depends Upon
Being&rdquo;, <em>Analysis</em>, 74: 370&ndash;378.</li>

<li>MacBride, F. &nbsp;and F. Janssen-Lauret, 2022, &ldquo;Why Lewis
Would Have Rejected Grounding&rdquo; in H.Beebee and A. Fischer, eds.,
<em>Perspectives on the Philosophy of David. K. Lewis</em>, Oxford:
Oxford University Press, 66&ndash;01.</li>

<li>Martin, C. B., 1980, &ldquo;Substance Substantiated,&rdquo;
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 58: 3&ndash;20.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, &ldquo;How It Is: Entities, Absences
and Voids,&rdquo; <em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 74:
57&ndash;65.</li>

<li>McGrath, M., 2003, &ldquo;What the Deflationist May Say About
Truthmaking,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy and Phenomenological Research</em>,
66: 666&ndash;688.</li>

<li>Melia, J., 2005, &ldquo;Truth-making without Truth-makers&rdquo;
in Beebee &amp; Dodd 2005a: 67&ndash;84.</li>

<li>Mellor, D. H., 1995, <em>The Facts of Causation</em>, London:
Routledge.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, &ldquo;<em>Real Metaphysics</em>:
Replies,&rdquo; in Lillehammer &amp; Rodriguez-Pereyra 2003:
212&ndash;6.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Truthmakers for What?,&rdquo;
in H. Dyke (e.d.) &amp; <em>From Truth to Reality: New Essays in Logic
&amp; Metaphysics</em> London: Francis &amp; Taylor.</li>

<li>Merricks, T., 2007, <em>Truth and Ontology</em>, Oxford: Clarendon
Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &ldquo;Replies to Cameron, Schaffer,
and Soames,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical Books</em>, 49:
328&ndash;343.</li>

<li>Miller, Kristie, and James Norton, 2017, &ldquo;Grounding:
It&rsquo;s (Probably) All in the Head,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical
Studies</em>, 174: 3059&ndash;3081.</li>

<li>Milne, P., 2005, &ldquo;Not Every Truth has a Truth-maker,&rdquo;
<em>Analysis</em>, 65: 221&ndash;224.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;Not Every Truth has a
Truth-maker II,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 73: 473&ndash;81.</li>

<li>Molnar, G., 2000, &ldquo;Truth-makers for Negative Truths,&rdquo;
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 78: 72&ndash;85.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2003, <em>Powers</em>, Stephen Mumford
(ed.), Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Monnoyer, J.M. (ed.), 2007 <em>Metaphysics and Truth-makers</em>,
Frankfurt: Ontos Verlag.</li>

<li>Mulligan, K., 2003, &ldquo;Stati di cose, verita&#768; e fattori
di verita&#768;,&rdquo; <em>Sistemi Intelligenti</em>, XV:
539&ndash;556.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Ascent, Propositions and other
Formal Objects,&rdquo; <em>Grazer Philosophische Studien</em>, 72:
29&ndash;48.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, &ldquo;Two Dogmas of
Truth-making,&rdquo; in Monnoyer, J. (ed.), 2007: 51&ndash;66.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Truth and the Truth-maker
Principle in 1921,&rdquo; Lowe and Rami 2009: 39&ndash;58.</li>

<li>Mulligan, K., P. Simons, and B. Smith, 1984,
&ldquo;Truth-Makers,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy and Phenomenological
Research</em>, 44: 287&ndash;321.</li>

<li>Prior, A. N., 1971, <em>Objects of Thought</em>, P. Geach and A.
Kenny (eds.), Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Raven, M.J., 2012, &ldquo;In Defence of Ground,&rdquo;
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 90: 687&ndash;701.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Ground,&rdquo; <em>Philosophy
Compass</em>, 10: 322&ndash;333.</li>

<li>Read, S., 2000, &ldquo;Truth-makers and the Disjunction
Thesis,&rdquo; <em>Mind</em>, 109: 67&ndash;79.</li>

<li>Restall, G., 1996, &ldquo;Truth-makers, Entailment and
Necessity,&rdquo; <em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 74:
331&ndash;340.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Modelling Truthmaking,&rdquo;
<em>Logique et Analyse</em>, 169&ndash;70: 211&ndash;30.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Post-script to
&lsquo;Truth-makers, Entailment and Necessity&rsquo;&rdquo; in Lowe
&amp; Rami 2009: 98&ndash;101.</li>

<li>Robinson, D., 2000, &ldquo;Identities, Distinctnesses,
Truth-makers, and Indiscernibility Principles,&rdquo; <em>Logique et
Analyse</em>, 43(169&ndash;170): 145&ndash;183.</li>

<li>Rodriguez-Pereyra G., 2005, &ldquo;Why Truth-makers,&rdquo; in
Beebee &amp; Dodd 2005a: 17&ndash;31.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006a, &ldquo;Truth-making, Entailment, and
the Conjunction Thesis,&rdquo; <em>Mind</em>, 115: 957&ndash;982.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006b, &ldquo;Truth-makers,&rdquo;
<em>Philosophy Compass</em>, 1: 186&ndash;200.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006c, &ldquo;Truthmaker Maximalism
Defended,&rdquo; <em>Analysis</em>, 66: 260&ndash;64</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;The Disjunction and
Conjunction Theses,&rdquo; <em>Mind</em>, 118: 427&ndash;443.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;Grounding is Not a Strict
Order,&rdquo; <em>Journal of the American Philosophical
Association</em>, 1: 517&ndash;534.</li>

<li>Ruben, D., 1990, <em>Explaining Explanation</em>, London:
Routledge.</li>

<li>Russell, B., 1918&ndash;19, &ldquo;The Philosophy of Logical
Atomism,&rdquo; <em>The Monist</em>, 28: 495&ndash;527; 29:
190&ndash;222, 345&ndash;380.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1919, &ldquo;On Propositions: What They
Are, and How They Mean&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian
Society</em> (Supplementary Volume), 2: 1&ndash;43.</li>

<li>Saenz, N.B., 2018, &ldquo;An account of truthmaking,&rdquo;
<em>Synthese</em>, https://doi.org/10.1007/s11229-018-1894-5</li>

<li>Sainsbury, R. M., 1995, <em>Paradoxes</em>, (2nd edition).
Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Schaffer, J., 2008a, &ldquo;Truth-maker Commitments,&rdquo;
<em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 141: 7&ndash;19.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008b, &ldquo;Truth and Fundamentality: On
Merricks&rsquo; <em>Truth and Ontology</em>,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical
Books</em>, 49: 302&ndash;16.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;On What Grounds What,&rdquo;
in D. Chalmers, D. Manley, and R. Wasserman (eds.),
<em>Metametaphysics</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press,
347&ndash;83.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, &ldquo;The Least Discerning and Most
Promiscuous Truth-maker,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical Quarterly</em>, 60:
307&ndash;24.</li>

<li>Schmutz, J., 2007, &ldquo;R&eacute;alistes, nihilistes et
incompatibilistes. Le d&eacute;bat sur les negative truth-makers dans
la scolastique j&eacute;suite espagnole,&rdquo; in J. Laurent (ed.),
<em>Dire le n&eacute;ant</em>, Caen: Presses Universitaires de Caen,
131&ndash;178.</li>

<li>Schnieder, B., 2006a, &ldquo;Truth-Making without
Truth-Makers,&rdquo; <em>Synthese</em>, 152: 21&ndash;46.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006b, &ldquo;Troubles with Truth-Making:
Necessitation and Projection,&rdquo; <em>Erkenntnis</em>, 64:
61&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Schulte, P., 2011a, &ldquo;Can Truthmaker Theorists Claim
Ontological Free Lunches?,&rdquo; <em>European Journal of
Philosophy</em>, 22: 249&ndash;68.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011b, &ldquo;Truthmakers: A Tale of Two
Explanatory Projects,&rdquo; <em>Synthese</em>, 181:
413&ndash;31.</li>

<li>Schipper, Arthur. 2018, &ldquo;Aboutness and negative truths: a
modest strategy for truthmaker theorists,&rdquo; <em>Synthese</em>,
195: 3685&ndash;3722.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Aboutness and ontology: a
modest approach to truthmakers,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical Studies</em>,
177: 505&ndash;533.</li>

<li>Sider, T., 2001, <em>Four-Dimensionalism</em>, Oxford:
Clarendon.</li>

<li>Simons, P., 1992, &ldquo;Logical Atomism and Its Ontological
Refinement: A Defense,&rdquo; in K. Mulligan (ed.), <em>Language,
Truth and Ontology</em>, Dordrecht: Kluwer, 157&ndash;179.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, &ldquo;How the World can Make
Propositions True: A Celebration of Logical Atomism,&rdquo; in M.
Omyla (ed.), <em>Sklonnosci Metafizyczna</em>, Warsaw: Uniwersytet
Warzawski, 113&ndash;135.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, &ldquo;Truth-maker Optimalism,&rdquo;
<em>Logique et Analyse</em>, 43(169&ndash;170): 17&ndash;41.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &ldquo;Negatives, Numbers, and
Necessity: Some Worries about Armstrong&rsquo;s Version of
Truth-making,&rdquo; <em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 83:
253&ndash;261.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &ldquo;Why the Negations of False
Atomic Sentences are True,&rdquo; in T. De Mey &amp; M. Kein&auml;nen
(eds.), <em>Essays on Armstrong</em>, <em>Acta Philosophica
Fennica</em>, 84: 15&ndash;36.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, &ldquo;Relations and
Truth-making,&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society</em>
(Supplementary Volumes), 84: 199&ndash;213.</li>

<li>Simpson, M., 2014, &ldquo;Defending Truthmaker
Non-Maximalism,&rdquo; <em>Thought</em>, 3: 288&ndash;291.</li>

<li>Skiles, A., 2014, &ldquo;Is there a dilemma for the truthmaker
non-maximalist?,&rdquo; <em>Synthese</em>, 191: 3649&ndash;3659</li>

<li>Smith, B., 1999, &ldquo;Truth-maker Realism,&rdquo;
<em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 77: 274&ndash;291.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &ldquo;Truth-maker Realism: Response
to Gregory,&rdquo; <em>Australasian Journal of Philosophy</em>, 80:
231&ndash;234.</li>

<li>Talasiewicz, Mieszko, Joanna Odrowaz-Sypniewska, Wojciech Wciorka,
and Piotr Wilkin, 2013, &ldquo;Do We Need a New Theory of Truthmaking?
Some Comments on Disjunction Thesis, Conjunction Thesis, Entailment
Principle and Explanation,&rdquo; <em>Philosophical Studies</em>, 165:
591&ndash;604.</li>

<li>Tallant, J., 2018, <em>Truth and the World: An Explanationist
Approach</em>, Abingdon, Routledge.</li>

<li>Tarski, A., 1933, &ldquo;The Concept of Truth in Formalised
Languages,&rdquo; in his 1956 <em>Logic, Semantics,
Metamathematics</em>, J. H. Woodger (trans.), Oxford: Clarendon.</li>

<li>Taylor, R., 1952, &ldquo;Negative Things,&rdquo; <em>The Journal
of Philosophy</em>, 49: 433&ndash;449.</li>

<li>Thomas, A., 2011, &ldquo;Deflationism and the Dependence of Truth
on Reality,&rdquo; <em>Erkenntnis</em>, 75: 113&ndash;122.</li>

<li>Veber, B., 2007, &ldquo;How to derive a &lsquo;not&rsquo; from an
&lsquo;is&rsquo;: a defence of the incompatibility view of negative
truths,&rdquo; <em>Metaphysica</em>, 9: 79&ndash;81.</li>

<li>Vision, G., 2005, &ldquo;Deflationary Truthmaking,&rdquo;
<em>European Journal of Philosophy</em>, 13: 364&ndash;380.</li>

<li>Williamson, T., 1999, &ldquo;Truthmakers and the Converse Barcan
Formula,&rdquo; <em>Dialectica</em>, 53: 253&ndash;70.</li>

<li>Wilson, J., 2014, &ldquo;No Work for a Theory of Grounding,&rdquo;
<em>Inquiry</em>, 57: 535&ndash;79.</li>

<li>Wittgenstein, L., 1921, <em>Tractatus Logico-Philosophicus</em>,
C.K. Ogden (trans.), London: Routledge &amp; Kegan Paul.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1953, <em>Philosophical
Investigations</em>, G.E.M. Anscombe (trans.), Oxford: Blackwell
Publishers Ltd.</li>
</ul>
